data.value:
Arles, one of the places to see in France, is located in Southern France. Its narrow streets and small squares are enough to make the feel of the Middle Ages. Arles is also the place where the artist Vincent Van Gogh lived for a while in 1888 and cut off his ear with iraq. That's why his name is often referred to as a master painter.
The Roman amphitheater, which has a rich historical heritage, is one of the places to visit. Cryptoporticus and Obelisk are examples of other Gallo-Roman structures of Arles. Saint Trophime Church is also worth a visit if you visit the city. The closest cities to Lyon or Marseille.
